The evidence with the title 'Governorship of Mitt Romney - Wikipedia ' says Mitt Romney was sworn in as the 70th governor of Massachusetts on january 2, 2003 , along with lieutenant governor Kerry Healey. Romney's term ended on january 4 , 2007; he chose not to run for re-election  ... 2002 , Romney proposed a plan that he said would balance the Massachusetts budget without raising taxes . 
